<ul><li>The&nbsp;<b>source code</b>&nbsp;is input as data to the compiler.</li><li>Which&nbsp;<b>scans through it</b>&nbsp;several times.</li><li>Each time performing&nbsp;<b>different checks</b>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<b>building up tables of information</b>&nbsp;needed to produce the final <b>object code</b>.</li><li>The object code can then be saved and run&nbsp;<b>without the presence of the compiler</b>.</li></ul>